IT Budget




Old Dominion Freight Line Inc. was founded in 1934 in Richmond, VA, and is now based in Thomasville, NC. The corporation serves over 48,000 direct points in North America, holding over 5,500 tractors, 15,600 trailers and 5,600 vans.  The company… MoreOld Dominion Freight Line Inc. was founded in 1934 in Richmond, VA, and is now based in Thomasville, NC. The corporation serves over 48,000 direct points in North America, holding over 5,500 tractors, 15,600 trailers and 5,600 vans.  The company also maintains operations in China, Canada, South America, and Southeast Asia.
Old Dominion Freight Line Inc. was founded in 1934 in Richmond, VA, and is now based in Thomasville, NC. The corporation serves over 48,000 direct points in North America, holding over 5,500 tractors, 15,600 trailers and 5,600 vans.  The company… MoreOld Dominion Freight Line Inc. was founded in 1934 in Richmond, VA, and is now based in Thomasville, NC. The corporation serves over 48,000 direct points in North America, holding over 5,500 tractors, 15,600 trailers and 5,600 vans.  The company also maintains operations in China, Canada, South America, and Southeast Asia.

IT Priorities:
•Old Dominion Freight Line Inc. (ODFL) is currently working to upgrade its SAP environment.
•The company's IT department is primarily focused on the support for the company's SAP-based supply-chain systems and its network infrastructure, which supports data and communications connections with the company's mobile trucking operations and distribution centers.
•ODFL is currently upgrading its EDI systems.

IT Structure:
•A Technology Services team is responsible for the company's IT project management, business intelligence systems, database activities.
•A separate team of programmers works with the services group to manage the freight processing applications that support core business operations, including on-board computing systems and operational monitoring applications.
•Outside of the IT department, an auditing team handles internal auditing and compliance efforts.

IT Intelligence Snippets:
•The company utilizes Cisco, BlackBerry, and Novell systems for its voice and data services.
•While ODFL is largely an SAP shop, it does utilize IBM systems and hardware to support its operations.
•Virtualization is handled with VMware solutions.





