Old Dominion Freight Line Announces a 21.4% Increase in Second-Quarter Earnings Per Diluted Share to $1.19 on Revenue of $839.9 Million | EON: Enhanced Online News






























News
Resources




























Old Dominion Freight Line Announces a 21.4% Increase in 
      Second-Quarter Earnings Per Diluted Share to $1.19 on Revenue of $839.9 
      Million




Operating Ratio Improves 140 Basis Points to Quarterly Company 
      Record of 80.9%




                    	July 27, 2017 07:00 AM Eastern Daylight Time 
                    	



THOMASVILLE, N.C.--(EON: Enhanced Online News)--Old Dominion Freight Line, Inc. (NASDAQ: ODFL) today announced financial 
      results for the three-month and six-month periods ended June 30, 2017, 
      which include the following:
    
“Old Dominion produced strong financial results for the second quarter 
      of 2017, which included a double-digit increase in revenue and an 
      increase of more than 20% in earnings per diluted share”





           
        

           
        

           
        



           
        

           
        



           
        

           
        



           
        

           
        













